In <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../323/5323.xml">
computer science</link>, a <b>single address space operating system</b> (or <b>SASOS</b>) is a type of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../194/22194.xml">
operating system</link> with simple <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../924/66924.xml">
memory management</link> which uses only one globally shared <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../423/934423.xml">
virtual address space</link>.
